 one of the marked zones gives way.\n\nToday's calendar carries direct event risk — US inflation data tends to move real yields, and silver is historically the more volatile of the two precious metals around these releases. A decisive daily close beyond either boundary of the range would strengthen the directional read; continued rejection at the extremes keeps the consolidation narrative intact.\n\nTHIS PAGE SHOWS AN ILLUSTRATIVE SAMPLE. The live trading desk analysis, generated from real market data, publishes every trading morning at 06:30 UK.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.","sample":true}